Tong, your hair!

11
00:00:39,880 --> 00:00:41,246
Try looking at the shelf above.

12
00:00:51,449 --> 00:00:52,891
Can you find it, Miss On?

13
00:00:56,188 --> 00:00:57,909
No.

14
00:01:03,527 --> 00:01:04,337
Pimnara.

15
00:01:06,036 --> 00:01:09,356
Are you sure you put it here?

16
00:01:09,741 --> 00:01:12,071
I’m positive I left it here.

17
00:01:12,986 --> 00:01:15,316
That’s right. I’m her witness.

18
00:01:15,640 --> 00:01:17,894
We saw it here just yesterday.

19
00:01:18,619 --> 00:01:19,894
But it’s gone.

20
00:01:20,908 --> 00:01:21,953
That was a lot of money.

21
00:01:22,663 --> 00:01:24,005
Why are you so careless?

22
00:01:24,563 --> 00:01:25,997
I apologize.

23
00:01:27,138 --> 00:01:30,476
Who else in the class knows that you left the money here?

24
00:01:32,378 --> 00:01:33,807
Everyone knows.

25
00:01:35,937 --> 00:01:39,277
Then the one who took the money

26
00:01:41,559 --> 00:01:42,877
must be someone from the class.

27
00:01:45,768 --> 00:01:46,452
Follow me.

28
00:02:58,068 --> 00:03:00,481
GRADUATION

29
00:03:03,386 --> 00:03:04,879
How can the class’s money disappear?

30
00:03:06,289 --> 00:03:07,444
Someone must have taken it.

31
00:03:08,509 --> 00:03:11,810
Whoever took the money

32
00:03:12,697 --> 00:03:13,884
had better turn themselves in right now.

33
00:03:14,239 --> 00:03:17,014
Otherwise, everyone in the class

34
00:03:18,459 --> 00:03:19,610
shall be punished.

35
00:03:23,083 --> 00:03:24,379
I’m giving you the chance.

36
00:03:27,341 --> 00:03:28,707
Does anyone feel the urge to own up to their action?

37
00:03:30,054 --> 00:03:32,967
If no one’s going to own up to it, that’s fine.

38
00:03:33,429 --> 00:03:38,142
Everyone, bring out a piece of paper and a pen

39
00:03:38,964 --> 00:03:43,880
then write down 3 names of the person you suspect to be the thief.

40
00:03:44,650 --> 00:03:46,168
The one whose name was mentioned most often

41
00:03:46,966 --> 00:03:48,966
will have to give their bag up for me to search.

42
00:03:49,535 --> 00:03:50,414
Sir.

43
00:03:51,680 --> 00:03:53,380
What right have you to suspect us?

44
00:03:55,180 --> 00:03:59,309
I’m your homeroom teacher, why can’t I suspect you guys?

45
00:04:00,000 --> 00:04:01,520
Especially when you’re our homeroom teacher,

46
00:04:02,052 --> 00:04:03,501
don’t you have to trust your students?

47
00:04:05,000 --> 00:04:08,084
Do you want to get punished so badly, Tong?

48
00:04:08,388 --> 00:04:09,675
That’s because you’re blaming the students.

49
00:04:10,410 --> 00:04:13,364
How dare you guys talk to me like that?

50
00:04:14,074 --> 00:04:16,265
I’m the grown-up, you are just kids.

51
00:04:16,265 --> 00:04:17,381
You’re not supposed to address me like that.

52
00:04:17,381 --> 00:04:19,198
Why does it have to be that adults are always right?

53
00:04:19,716 --> 00:04:21,006
Do kids have to be on the wrong all the time?

54
00:04:21,935 --> 00:04:22,633
Tong.

55
00:04:23,216 --> 00:04:24,188
You’re the worst one.

56
00:04:24,747 --> 00:04:28,319
You’re the one I’m most suspicious of among all the people in this class.

57
00:04:30,286 --> 00:04:33,200
Excuse me, but you have no right to do this.

58
00:04:34,297 --> 00:04:34,934
Why?

59
00:04:35,720 --> 00:04:36,627
What don’t I have the right to?

60
00:04:37,918 --> 00:04:40,560
You don’t have the right to make us write and vote.

61
00:04:41,184 --> 00:04:44,163
You don’t have the right to make us suspect other students in the class.

62
00:04:44,593 --> 00:04:47,745
Even though the money is gone, we can collect it again.

63
00:04:49,114 --> 00:04:50,000
That’s true.

64
00:04:51,200 --> 00:04:52,768
We can gather up the money again.

65
00:04:52,768 --> 00:04:53,894
Pimnara.

66
00:04:55,163 --> 00:04:58,481
You are the class’ president yet you dare go against my command?

67
00:04:59,451 --> 00:05:00,188
Yes.

68
00:05:01,151 --> 00:05:02,617
As a class president,

69
00:05:03,526 --> 00:05:05,323
I’m protecting my fellow classmates.

70
00:05:12,710 --> 00:05:14,203
We’re not thieves, sir.

71
00:05:14,760 --> 00:05:17,166
That’s right, we’re not thieves, sir.

72
00:05:17,546 --> 00:05:19,546
You can’t blame us like this.

73
00:05:20,657 --> 00:05:21,494
That’s right.

74
00:05:21,950 --> 00:05:23,519
You don’t have the right to do this to us.

75
00:05:24,724 --> 00:05:25,680
We’re not accepting this.

76
00:05:25,680 --> 00:05:26,344
Hey!

77
00:05:27,171 --> 00:05:28,664
You guys are beyond yourselves.

78
00:05:29,009 --> 00:05:30,654
How dare you raise your voice with a grown-up.

79
00:05:30,654 --> 00:05:32,318
But the grown-up is the one who’s blaming the kids.

80
00:05:50,027 --> 00:05:50,666
Tong.

81
00:05:51,604 --> 00:05:54,704
Everyone, I command you to sit down, right now.

82
00:05:55,414 --> 00:05:56,221
No.

83
00:06:10,242 --> 00:06:11,724
I told you to sit down.

84
00:06:12,864 --> 00:06:14,610
Sit down, this is a command.

85
00:07:07,893 --> 00:07:10,121
Stop staring at me already.

86
00:07:12,092 --> 00:07:16,551
If my parents saw this, I would be scolded.

87
00:07:18,304 --> 00:07:20,000
There’s nothing wrong with it.

88
00:07:20,447 --> 00:07:22,086
I think you’re cool.

89
00:07:25,379 --> 00:07:26,581
Don’t be sad, Lin.

90
00:07:27,379 --> 00:07:30,262
I think you’re a very cool class present.

91
00:07:30,845 --> 00:07:35,317
Yes, getting punished for protecting your classmates is so awesome, Lin.

92
00:07:36,255 --> 00:07:37,214
Lin.

93
00:07:37,873 --> 00:07:39,792
You’re the best class president.

94
00:07:42,632 --> 00:07:44,780
Ever since I’ve known you since middle school

95
00:07:45,377 --> 00:07:48,178
,I’ve just realized now that you’re this awesome.

96
00:07:50,000 --> 00:07:53,496
you’re so damn cool.

97
00:07:54,175 --> 00:07:56,378
You’re cool even when you’re crying.

98
00:07:57,823 --> 00:07:59,823
How is it cool?

99
00:08:01,339 --> 00:08:03,339
You’re so damn cool.

100
00:08:04,280 --> 00:08:06,686
No, I’m not.

101
00:08:06,686 --> 00:08:08,822
You’re really cool, Lin

102
00:08:09,694 --> 00:08:11,694
(I don’t think life is like taking tests.)

103
00:08:12,730 --> 00:08:14,578
(We might not find the right answer.)

104
00:08:17,740 --> 00:08:19,280
You’re so awesome, Lin.

105
00:08:25,241 --> 00:08:29,054
(Back then, no one knows who took the money.)

106
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,113
(But I don’t care.)

107
00:08:32,203 --> 00:08:34,172
(Because the only thing I could remember on that day,)

108
00:08:36,226 --> 00:08:37,890
(was Lin’s courage)(

109
00:08:40,000 --> 00:08:41,517
that was stamped onto my mind.)

110
00:08:45,345 --> 00:08:47,994
FINAL EXAM’S DAY.

111
00:08:50,479 --> 00:08:52,046
Done with the exams!

112
00:08:56,204 --> 00:08:57,458
Finally done with the 12th grade!

113
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:01,648
No more studying!

114
00:09:02,921 --> 00:09:04,313
Yay!

115
00:09:04,313 --> 00:09:05,606
Hey, hey, calm down.

116
00:09:05,892 --> 00:09:07,193
We still have the University Entrance Exam.

117
00:09:07,370 --> 00:09:08,069
Huh?

118
00:09:08,272 --> 00:09:08,863
Huh?

119
00:09:09,046 --> 00:09:09,774
What are you ‘huh’ing for?

120
00:09:09,774 --> 00:09:10,640
You could fail to get into university.

121
00:09:11,594 --> 00:09:12,243
He’s right.

122
00:09:12,851 --> 00:09:13,860
Help me gather up these notes.

123
00:09:13,860 --> 00:09:15,000
Why the heck did you throw it?

124
00:09:19,588 --> 00:09:22,958
You guys do act like a child from primary to graduating high school.

125
00:09:24,581 --> 00:09:27,798
But there’s someone who behaves like a giraffe

126
00:09:27,798 --> 00:09:29,466
from kindergarten to graduating high school.

127
00:09:36,024 --> 00:09:41,142
Help!

128
00:09:41,142 --> 00:09:42,616
Did you ask for help?

129
00:09:43,573 --> 00:09:44,405
How was it?

130
00:09:44,405 --> 00:09:45,396
Could you figure the questions out?

131
00:09:46,324 --> 00:09:48,654
I did the exercises you gave me

132
00:09:49,220 --> 00:09:50,116
so I was able to solve all the questions.

133
00:09:50,522 --> 00:09:52,313
Really? Great job.

134
00:09:58,423 --> 00:10:00,272
Hey, don’t bully your friend.

135
00:10:00,272 --> 00:10:02,600
Don’t.

136
00:10:03,136 --> 00:10:04,097
Ja-Oh.

137
00:10:06,067 --> 00:10:07,788
I’m going down the stairs~

138
00:10:13,423 --> 00:10:14,738
6 years ago

139
00:10:16,310 --> 00:10:17,954
when we were just kids,

140
00:10:20,261 --> 00:10:22,593
we get to take different classes,

141
00:10:23,911 --> 00:10:25,360
learn about the life,

142
00:10:27,185 --> 00:10:29,291
learn about friendship from friends,

143
00:10:31,090 --> 00:10:32,659
learn about mistakes,

144
00:10:34,703 --> 00:10:36,627
and learn to dream.

145
00:10:38,874 --> 00:10:40,440
But today,

146
00:10:40,941 --> 00:10:45,705
the kids from that day are about to leave the school

147
00:10:46,133 --> 00:10:48,133
as an adult.

148
00:10:51,856 --> 00:10:57,304
Until that day, the day when our dreams come true,

149
00:10:58,368 --> 00:11:02,523
the day we get to become the adults we dreamed of,

150
00:11:07,774 --> 00:11:10,284
When I think of not being able to see you guys again,

151
00:11:10,690 --> 00:11:12,548
it makes my heart sink.

152
00:11:21,219 --> 00:11:30,479
I hope everyone will keep the time and days in this school

153
00:11:31,926 --> 00:11:33,926
in their memory forever.

154
00:11:46,519 --> 00:11:47,247
Ready?

155
00:11:47,247 --> 00:11:48,899
1…2…3…

156
00:11:48,899 --> 00:11:51,161
Let’s go!

157
00:12:07,094 --> 00:12:09,094
1…2…3…

158
00:12:09,094 --> 00:12:12,384
Hooray!

159
00:12:16,919 --> 00:12:22,266
(Back then, I didn’t understand why people were crying.)

160
00:12:23,216 --> 00:12:24,531
(We’re just graduating.)

161
00:12:24,891 --> 00:12:26,283
(It’s not like anyone’s dying.)

162
00:12:27,425 --> 00:12:28,817
(But when I grow up,)

163
00:12:29,361 --> 00:12:31,361
(I come to understand those tears.)

164
00:12:40,242 --> 00:12:41,786
Good luck, everyone.

165
00:12:46,898 --> 00:12:50,000
I hope we’ll get to meet again one day.

166
00:12:59,635 --> 00:13:04,348
(On that day, we didn’t cry because we were afraid we’d never meet again.)

167
00:13:05,000 --> 00:13:06,341
(We cried because we knew,)

168
00:13:07,279 --> 00:13:12,626
(we would never meet again with the same feeling.)

169
00:13:36,194 --> 00:13:37,600
I’m so jealous of you.

170
00:13:38,259 --> 00:13:41,742
You have boys trailing behind you from the first day until the graduation day.

171
00:13:43,517 --> 00:13:45,942
There’s nothing to be jealous of.

172
00:13:45,942 --> 00:13:47,070
Is that so?

173
00:13:47,070 --> 00:13:48,133
So which one are you choosing?

174
00:13:50,880 --> 00:13:51,778
Tell me.

175
00:13:51,778 --> 00:13:52,880
I won’t tell anyone.

176
00:13:55,622 --> 00:13:56,637
Fine.

177
00:14:02,342 --> 00:14:04,113
I knew it.

178
00:14:09,873 --> 00:14:11,290
Ja-Oh!

179
00:14:26,823 --> 00:14:29,431
She’s good with her words.

180
00:14:29,431 --> 00:14:31,413
Ja-Oh’s not only good at talking,

181
00:14:31,413 --> 00:14:32,240
she’s also a s—

182
00:14:33,662 --> 00:14:35,408
sweet talker.

183
00:14:57,828 --> 00:14:58,341
Here you go.

184
00:15:00,010 --> 00:15:00,873
No change, right?

185
00:15:08,915 --> 00:15:09,691
Tong!

186
00:15:09,799 --> 00:15:10,415
Hmm?

187
00:15:11,796 --> 00:15:12,965
Where did your dad go?

188
00:15:13,247 --> 00:15:15,569
He’s your husband, why are you asking the son?

189
00:15:15,569 --> 00:15:16,810
Are you trying to get on my nerves?

190
00:15:17,374 --> 00:15:18,572
Calm down.

191
00:15:18,572 --> 00:15:19,455
I’m just kidding.

192
00:15:19,589 --> 00:15:20,722
Where are you going?

193
00:15:21,069 --> 00:15:22,400
Your university entrance exams are coming up.

194
00:15:22,573 --> 00:15:24,609
Aren’t you going to study?

195
00:15:26,191 --> 00:15:28,026
I’m heading to a study session.

196
00:15:34,688 --> 00:15:35,712
You’re proud, aren’t you?

197
00:15:35,950 --> 00:15:37,728
That your son is so studious?

198
00:15:37,728 --> 00:15:38,678
Go, go.

199
00:15:38,678 --> 00:15:40,190
Just go wherever you want.

200
00:15:40,564 --> 00:15:41,256
Mom.

201
00:15:41,256 --> 00:15:41,756
Hmm?

202
00:15:41,756 --> 00:15:42,428
Come here for a second.

203
00:15:43,013 --> 00:15:43,834
Come here.

204
00:15:45,568 --> 00:15:46,266
I’m off now!

205
00:15:49,019 --> 00:15:51,124
Teach your dad to do something like this too.

206
00:15:54,939 --> 00:15:56,173
Buy me a new auto bike, Mom.

207
00:15:58,700 --> 00:16:00,700
I barely have enough to eat,

208
00:16:00,700 --> 00:16:01,983
yet you want me to buy you a new auto bike?

209
00:16:01,983 --> 00:16:02,868
You bastard.

210
00:16:08,104 --> 00:16:09,389
(After graduating from the 12th Grade,)

211
00:16:10,240 --> 00:16:12,240
(we have to get ready for the entrance exam.)

212
00:16:13,442 --> 00:16:17,870
(Everyone says that it’s the exam that decides your future)

213
00:16:18,964 --> 00:16:23,153
(and the person you will grow up to become from now on.)

214
00:16:30,135 --> 00:16:31,512
It’s as tasty as usual.

215
00:16:31,599 --> 00:16:32,309
Thank you.

216
00:16:32,309 --> 00:16:33,943
Please stop by again.

217
00:16:43,645 --> 00:16:46,100
Ja-Oh, you don’t have to help out here.

218
00:16:46,100 --> 00:16:47,538
Go and study for your exam.

219
00:16:48,556 --> 00:16:49,562
It’s alright, Mom.

220
00:16:49,562 --> 00:16:51,183
I can study later.

221
00:16:54,588 --> 00:16:56,244
Are you alright, Dad?

222
00:16:56,829 --> 00:16:58,247
Have you taken your medicine?

223
00:16:59,136 --> 00:16:59,984
I have, of course.

224
00:17:00,353 --> 00:17:01,332
I’m fine.

225
00:17:01,830 --> 00:17:02,909
Just a little cough.

226
00:17:03,830 --> 00:17:05,828
You should take good care of yourself.

227
00:17:06,088 --> 00:17:10,864
What would you do when I go to university and can’t look after you anymore?

228
00:17:13,441 --> 00:17:16,265
Don’t worry about me, just worry about yourself.

229
00:17:17,087 --> 00:17:19,390
Have you decided what you want to study?

230
00:17:21,550 --> 00:17:22,986
I can study anything.

231
00:17:23,252 --> 00:17:26,726
As long as I can get a high salary after graduating.

232
00:17:29,121 --> 00:17:30,709
Why are you thinking that way?

233
00:17:31,213 --> 00:17:34,102
Because if I’m rich, you guys would be able to live well.

234
00:17:35,195 --> 00:17:38,582
Should I study something to become the state’s officer?

235
00:17:39,179 --> 00:17:41,548
People say that the benefit is good, Dad.

236
00:17:43,410 --> 00:17:44,313
Ja-Oh,

237
00:17:45,527 --> 00:17:48,033
you don’t have to study for our sake.

238
00:17:49,176 --> 00:17:51,284
Just study whatever you want.

239
00:17:52,303 --> 00:17:53,609
It’s your life.

240
00:17:54,629 --> 00:17:56,174
It’s your dream.

241
00:17:56,808 --> 00:17:58,331
Not ours.

242
00:18:03,935 --> 00:18:05,935
Go ahead and study.

243
00:18:06,046 --> 00:18:07,677
We’ve got it covered here.

244
00:18:13,876 --> 00:18:15,247
Ja-Oh!

245
00:18:17,377 --> 00:18:18,149
Mai!

246
00:18:18,539 --> 00:18:19,803
What are you doing here?

247
00:18:19,803 --> 00:18:21,452
I’m taking my parents to have a meal here.

248
00:18:21,690 --> 00:18:22,346
Huh?

249
00:18:22,649 --> 00:18:23,808
At my restaurant?

250
00:18:23,808 --> 00:18:24,642
Yes.

251
00:18:25,444 --> 00:18:26,290
Pa. Ma.

252
00:18:26,875 --> 00:18:27,931
Coming.

253
00:18:28,314 --> 00:18:29,402
Be right there.

254
00:18:29,901 --> 00:18:31,095
Why are you in such a hurry, Mai?

255
00:18:31,095 --> 00:18:31,645
Hurry up.

256
00:18:32,686 --> 00:18:33,416
I’m here.

257
00:18:33,785 --> 00:18:35,055
Our entire house is here.

258
00:18:35,055 --> 00:18:36,720
We’re here as a family.

259
00:18:37,891 --> 00:18:38,691
Hello.

260
00:18:38,691 --> 00:18:39,891
Hello, hello.

261
00:18:39,891 --> 00:18:40,637
Hello.

262
00:18:40,637 --> 00:18:41,947
Please come in.

263
00:18:41,947 --> 00:18:43,066
Come, Pa, Ma.

264
00:18:44,149 --> 00:18:46,149
Hey, stop scratching.

265
00:18:47,116 --> 00:18:48,025
It’s itchy.

266
00:18:49,239 --> 00:18:50,590
Fine, fine, I’ll stop scratching.

267
00:18:54,884 --> 00:18:55,992
What would you like to have?

268
00:18:56,801 --> 00:18:58,178
Bring us whatever you recommend.

269
00:18:58,547 --> 00:19:00,493
I’d recommend you try Green Curry, Palo,

270
00:19:00,493 --> 00:19:02,722
and our restaurant’s special recipe of Nam Prik Ong.

271
00:19:02,722 --> 00:19:05,166
Guaranteed they’re delicious and good for your health.

272
00:19:05,798 --> 00:19:07,798
Oh my.

273
00:19:08,642 --> 00:19:11,509
She’s good with her words.

