319
00:21:16,616 --> 00:21:17,725
Oops. Toh, my boy.

320
00:21:19,481 --> 00:21:20,213
Shoot!

321
00:21:21,124 --> 00:21:22,872
Oops! I’m sorry, Mom.

322
00:21:25,538 --> 00:21:27,626
You’re taking the entrance exam soon, aren’t you going to study, Bank?

323
00:21:29,588 --> 00:21:33,626
The only ‘en’ I’m interested in is, NBA.

324
00:21:35,623 --> 00:21:38,028
If you can’t get into university, I’ll send you away.

325
00:21:38,028 --> 00:21:39,379
You’ll send me to America?

326
00:21:39,379 --> 00:21:41,735
I’ll send you far away from my face.

327
00:21:41,735 --> 00:21:42,702
Go and study already.

328
00:21:42,702 --> 00:21:43,561
Don’t just play.

329
00:21:45,612 --> 00:21:46,503
Let me play first.

330
00:21:47,612 --> 00:21:49,458
I’ve studied before, I can just do that later.

331
00:21:51,669 --> 00:21:52,779
Mom, scream for me.

332
00:21:53,191 --> 00:21:55,628
There we go, we’ve got a girl screaming for me.

333
00:21:55,736 --> 00:21:56,739
Oh ho!

334
00:21:58,148 --> 00:21:59,145
The first girl is Mom, though.

335
00:22:06,108 --> 00:22:08,108
Eat up, my Meatball.

336
00:22:08,108 --> 00:22:10,039
So you’ll have the strength to study.

337
00:22:10,165 --> 00:22:11,165
Thank you, Ma.

338
00:22:11,534 --> 00:22:15,108
I promise to get into a good university and go study abroad.

339
00:22:15,229 --> 00:22:16,774
My!

340
00:22:16,774 --> 00:22:21,067
Our meatball’s going to become the first person in our family to graduate from abroad?

341
00:22:21,564 --> 00:22:22,405
That’s right, Ma.

342
00:22:22,578 --> 00:22:24,470
I’ll be the pride of our family.

343
00:22:24,470 --> 00:22:27,440
I will not disappoint Pa because I will not fool around with life

344
00:22:27,440 --> 00:22:29,417
just as Pa said before he passed away.

345
00:22:30,765 --> 00:22:34,588
Papa must be smiling from ear to ear in heaven right now.

346
00:22:34,781 --> 00:22:36,087
That’s great, Son.

347
00:22:36,548 --> 00:22:39,588
But before anything else, an army marches on its stomach.

348
00:22:39,850 --> 00:22:41,748
Eat up, eat a lot.

349
00:22:41,748 --> 00:22:43,256
Tell me whatever you want to eat.

350
00:22:43,256 --> 00:22:43,756
Sure, Ma.

351
00:22:43,756 --> 00:22:44,383
I’ll cater it to you.

352
00:22:44,383 --> 00:22:45,346
Sure, Ma.

353
00:22:45,346 --> 00:22:46,746
Thank you.

354
00:23:01,660 --> 00:23:02,733
Meatball!

355
00:23:02,733 --> 00:23:04,588
Meatball, my baby!

356
00:23:04,588 --> 00:23:05,414
Meatball!

357
00:23:06,142 --> 00:23:08,142
Help!

358
00:23:08,142 --> 00:23:09,699
Help my son!

359
00:23:09,699 --> 00:23:10,199
Meatball!

360
00:23:10,199 --> 00:23:10,986
Ma’am, here are the meatballs.

361
00:23:10,986 --> 00:23:12,371
Not these!

362
00:23:12,371 --> 00:23:13,358
Meatball!

363
00:23:13,358 --> 00:23:14,586
- Meatball!
- Help!

364
00:23:14,586 --> 00:23:16,858
Help Meatball!

365
00:23:17,548 --> 00:23:19,548
Help!

366
00:23:21,837 --> 00:23:23,490
Meatball!

367
00:23:23,739 --> 00:23:25,428
Meatball!

368
00:23:26,290 --> 00:23:31,217
Meatball!

369
00:23:34,228 --> 00:23:35,252
My son!

370
00:23:37,764 --> 00:23:40,241
You almost get to meet your Papa in heaven.

371
00:23:41,641 --> 00:23:42,839
Here are some more meatballs.

372
00:23:43,253 --> 00:23:44,588
I wasn’t talking about this meatball.

373
00:23:44,588 --> 00:23:45,253
Go!

374
00:24:08,211 --> 00:24:11,295
I never thought I would see my son studying like the others.

375
00:24:12,006 --> 00:24:13,703
I’ve always liked reading, actually.

376
00:24:15,001 --> 00:24:16,116
Is that so?

377
00:24:16,289 --> 00:24:21,022
That means you’ll get into a good university and make us proud, right?

378
00:24:21,781 --> 00:24:23,275
But I don’t know what I want to study yet.

379
00:24:24,077 --> 00:24:25,726
Anywhere that you manage to get into.

380
00:24:27,590 --> 00:24:29,269
“Any” is a broad term.

381
00:24:30,505 --> 00:24:31,852
I don’t know what I want to do for work yet.

382
00:24:33,413 --> 00:24:36,639
You have to think of what you want to do.

383
00:24:37,047 --> 00:24:39,806
You don’t like thinking about stuff like this ever since you were a child.

384
00:24:40,175 --> 00:24:41,344
It’d be nice if you’d give it a try.

385
00:24:43,772 --> 00:24:44,386
By the way,

386
00:24:45,106 --> 00:24:46,499
have you seen your dad around?

387
00:24:46,499 --> 00:24:48,003
He’s been missing since the morning.

388
00:24:49,743 --> 00:24:52,709
He’s probably out to buy something to make it up to you.

389
00:24:54,920 --> 00:24:57,221
Then go back to your reading, I won’t get in the way.

390
00:25:20,655 --> 00:25:21,298
Cheers.

391
00:25:21,471 --> 00:25:23,024
Why do you have so many things to celebrate?

392
00:25:23,024 --> 00:25:23,939
What’s the occasion?

393
00:25:23,939 --> 00:25:26,340
We need to celebrate our boy graduating high school.

394
00:25:26,340 --> 00:25:27,791
So I invited friends for some drinks.

395
00:25:27,791 --> 00:25:29,240
Why aren’t you going home?

396
00:25:48,517 --> 00:25:49,257
CLOSED FOR A DAY.

397
00:25:49,257 --> 00:25:52,372
Come on, cheers.

398
00:25:52,502 --> 00:25:53,719
Don’t just stay still there.

399
00:25:54,647 --> 00:25:55,833
We’ve just gotten started.

400
00:25:57,217 --> 00:26:01,798
I’m curious, what are we celebrating?

401
00:26:01,798 --> 00:26:04,160
You forced me to close my shop since noon.

402
00:26:04,160 --> 00:26:05,043
You know nothing.

403
00:26:05,469 --> 00:26:10,211
To celebrate my son and Chen’s son graduating from high school.

404
00:26:12,018 --> 00:26:13,136
I’m so proud.

405
00:26:13,136 --> 00:26:14,611
Talking about which, though,

406
00:26:14,611 --> 00:26:18,460
I can’t believe my son, Dong, would graduate high school like the others.

407
00:26:18,460 --> 00:26:18,986
Right.

408
00:26:19,208 --> 00:26:21,075
I thought he was dumb just like you are.

409
00:26:22,272 --> 00:26:24,433
I only see him getting in and out of Haeb’s place.

410
00:26:24,433 --> 00:26:25,931
What’s up with my place?

411
00:26:25,931 --> 00:26:26,710
What’s up with it?

412
00:26:26,710 --> 00:26:27,396
That’s right.

413
00:26:27,396 --> 00:26:30,166
His place is full of entertainment.

414
00:26:30,166 --> 00:26:30,666
That’s right.

415
00:26:30,666 --> 00:26:33,421
All the dirty and nasty things happen at Haeb’s.

416
00:26:33,795 --> 00:26:35,177
How could you say that, are you out of your mind?

417
00:26:35,177 --> 00:26:37,106
Come, cheers!

418
00:26:37,362 --> 00:26:39,039
Let’s go all the way.

419
00:26:44,997 --> 00:26:45,981
Chen!

420
00:26:47,098 --> 00:26:48,531
Why aren’t you going home?

421
00:26:49,983 --> 00:26:51,434
I definitely will be going back home.

422
00:26:51,434 --> 00:26:52,888
But I’m just meeting up with my friends for a bit.

423
00:26:52,888 --> 00:26:54,191
Why do you have so many things to celebrate?

424
00:26:54,191 --> 00:26:55,085
What’s the occasion?

425
00:26:55,408 --> 00:26:59,649
Babe, our son’s just graduated from high school so I’ve invited my friends for a drink.

426
00:27:00,536 --> 00:27:02,234
I know that you are glad.

427
00:27:02,617 --> 00:27:07,155
But can't you just have a little drink and get back to helping me with work?

428
00:27:07,663 --> 00:27:09,663
I normally stay at the shop, Babe.

429
00:27:09,663 --> 00:27:12,197
But let me have just today, to be with my friends for a day.

430
00:27:13,004 --> 00:27:13,573
Fine.

431
00:27:13,976 --> 00:27:16,639
You’re choosing your friends over me, huh?

432
00:27:18,151 --> 00:27:18,688
Fine.

433
00:27:18,989 --> 00:27:22,973
I’m announcing it right here with everyone as my witness.

434
00:27:23,235 --> 00:27:28,155
I’ve been giving it to you every night from 8 to 10 PM.

435
00:27:28,155 --> 00:27:30,625
But from now on, that’s not happening anymore.

436
00:27:30,625 --> 00:27:31,987
My dear wife!

437
00:27:31,987 --> 00:27:33,661
No, no. Please, don’t say that.

438
00:27:33,661 --> 00:27:35,871
Please don’t joke around about such a thing.

439
00:27:35,871 --> 00:27:36,422
Please?

440
00:27:36,422 --> 00:27:37,131
I’m begging you.

441
00:27:37,131 --> 00:27:38,807
You just said you’re choosing your friends over me.

442
00:27:38,807 --> 00:27:40,450
Those are two different things.

443
00:27:40,450 --> 00:27:41,685
I just wanted to be with my friends for a little while

444
00:27:41,685 --> 00:27:43,094
then I’ll get back to work.

445
00:27:43,094 --> 00:27:44,114
Can I have everything as it is?

446
00:27:44,195 --> 00:27:45,097
I have an offer.

447
00:27:45,922 --> 00:27:47,922
If you come home with me right now,

448
00:27:48,333 --> 00:27:51,946
I’ll give it to you non-stop from 8 PM to 5 AM.

449
00:27:51,946 --> 00:27:52,854
Are you taking it?

450
00:27:52,854 --> 00:27:53,851
Yes, I am.

451
00:27:54,392 --> 00:27:55,760
You really have to do it.

452
00:27:55,888 --> 00:27:56,674
Should I get undressed right here?

453
00:27:56,674 --> 00:27:57,702
Oh! No, no.

454
00:27:58,189 --> 00:27:58,871
Do you want it right here, right now?

455
00:27:58,871 --> 00:27:59,806
No, people are watching.

456
00:27:59,806 --> 00:28:00,526
Hey! Turn away.

457
00:28:00,526 --> 00:28:01,359
This is my wife.

458
00:28:01,462 --> 00:28:02,334
No, my dear wife.

459
00:28:02,334 --> 00:28:03,109
Don’t get undressed here.

460
00:28:03,109 --> 00:28:03,998
Let’s get undressed at home.

461
00:28:03,998 --> 00:28:04,509
Fine.

462
00:28:04,872 --> 00:28:05,785
Then follow me.

463
00:28:05,785 --> 00:28:06,337
Yes, yes.

464
00:28:06,337 --> 00:28:07,106
Hurry up.

465
00:28:07,106 --> 00:28:07,792
Yes.

466
00:28:09,203 --> 00:28:09,956
Alright, my friends.

467
00:28:09,956 --> 00:28:11,547
I love my friends but I’m choosing my wife.

468
00:28:11,645 --> 00:28:12,354
I’m off now.

469
00:28:13,080 --> 00:28:15,137
Wifey, wait for me!

470
00:28:15,260 --> 00:28:17,260
Oh, Chen.

471
00:28:17,637 --> 00:28:21,755
Husbands have to stay above their wives.

472
00:28:21,755 --> 00:28:23,431
if you’re under your wife’s control from the beginning,

473
00:28:23,431 --> 00:28:25,891
you will always be under her for the rest of your life.

474
00:28:25,891 --> 00:28:27,071
You have to stay above your wife.

475
00:28:27,071 --> 00:28:30,089
Look at me, my wife does not dare do anything to me.

476
00:28:30,445 --> 00:28:32,445
Because I’m above her.

477
00:28:32,445 --> 00:28:35,682
You guys have no idea how I treat my wife back at home.

478
00:28:36,883 --> 00:28:38,883
She doesn’t even dare say a word to me.

479
00:28:39,940 --> 00:28:42,222
Does she even dare do anything to me?

480
00:28:42,222 --> 00:28:47,011
I’m telling you, yesterday, we were having a meal and she was yapping too much.

481
00:28:47,011 --> 00:28:48,825
So I made her dine in tears.

482
00:28:50,769 --> 00:28:54,422
I’m telling you, if she ever has a problem, I’m kicking right up here.

483
00:28:54,914 --> 00:28:56,914
Right in the chin.

484
00:28:56,996 --> 00:28:59,635
When her nose bleeds like dip drops, dip drops,

485
00:28:59,635 --> 00:29:02,393
I’d take a glass to collect them and drink her blood up.

486
00:29:03,795 --> 00:29:05,621
I’m not Chen.

487
00:29:05,621 --> 00:29:06,656
Someone like Chen…

488
00:29:17,525 --> 00:29:18,395
I’ll just be dead.

489
00:29:20,290 --> 00:29:21,433
Hold on, Tao.

490
00:29:22,199 --> 00:29:23,826
You can’t just simply die.

491
00:29:29,916 --> 00:29:31,363
Well, well.

492
00:29:31,948 --> 00:29:33,304
Are you showing off to your friends?

493
00:29:33,949 --> 00:29:36,854
You said I was dining in tears.

494
00:29:37,136 --> 00:29:39,373
Were you telling the truth?

495
00:29:40,744 --> 00:29:41,704
I wasn’t.

496
00:29:42,551 --> 00:29:43,352
Khai,

497
00:29:44,038 --> 00:29:45,229
I wasn’t saying that, right?

498
00:29:45,511 --> 00:29:46,592
You did.

499
00:29:48,427 --> 00:29:49,398
That wasn’t all.

500
00:29:49,882 --> 00:29:53,606
You kicked right in my chin and my blood was dripping,

501
00:29:53,606 --> 00:29:55,678
Dip drops, dip drops.

502
00:29:56,162 --> 00:29:58,162
You said that, didn’t you?

503
00:29:59,782 --> 00:30:02,488
I must admit, I didn’t say that.

504
00:30:02,488 --> 00:30:04,411
I didn’t say that.

505
00:30:04,883 --> 00:30:06,253
You did.

506
00:30:08,249 --> 00:30:09,013
Clean up.

507
00:30:09,315 --> 00:30:10,629
Yes, ma’am.

508
00:30:19,441 --> 00:30:20,992
This is just a little indoor part.

509
00:30:21,597 --> 00:30:23,833
I’ll give you a big outdoor set when we go out.

510
00:30:23,833 --> 00:30:24,754
I’ll see you outside.

511
00:30:24,915 --> 00:30:25,555
Follow me.

512
00:30:33,354 --> 00:30:33,985
Khai.

513
00:30:34,812 --> 00:30:36,068
Can you come with me?

514
00:30:37,258 --> 00:30:38,608
I have to stay with him.

515
00:30:39,999 --> 00:30:42,158
Haeb, come with me.

516
00:30:44,154 --> 00:30:45,550
If I go, he’d be lonely.

517
00:30:59,383 --> 00:31:01,062
Do you plan to always keep on being studious?

518
00:31:03,421 --> 00:31:04,075
Yeah.

519
00:31:04,761 --> 00:31:06,235
I like studying.

520
00:31:07,122 --> 00:31:09,662
When I like anything, I should put my mind to it.

521
00:31:10,327 --> 00:31:12,127
That’s what my parents told me.

522
00:31:16,321 --> 00:31:18,428
If you like it so much, why don't you study all the way to PhD?

523
00:31:19,093 --> 00:31:20,626
That's what I'm planning to do.

524
00:31:22,239 --> 00:31:24,501
I think I'd study up to a PhD.

525
00:31:25,277 --> 00:31:27,927
I want to become the country’s best marine scientist.

526
00:31:29,520 --> 00:31:30,196
Wow.

527
00:31:31,850 --> 00:31:33,669
Don’t you have to be studying until you’re old?

528
00:31:35,342 --> 00:31:36,121
Hey.

529
00:31:36,121 --> 00:31:39,376
When it comes to studying, it doesn’t matter how old you are.

530
00:31:39,880 --> 00:31:41,108
There’s nothing to be ashamed of.

531
00:31:41,410 --> 00:31:42,927
That’s what my parents told me.

532
00:31:47,521 --> 00:31:49,077
And how long would it take

533
00:31:51,143 --> 00:31:55,482
until you’ve managed to become a marine scientist

534
00:31:57,845 --> 00:31:59,225
or whatever that you said?

535
00:32:00,959 --> 00:32:03,493
4 years of undergrads here.

536
00:32:03,594 --> 00:32:05,889
2 years of master’s degree abroad.

537
00:32:06,978 --> 00:32:09,340
And a minimum of 4 years for the PhD.

538
00:32:13,978 --> 00:32:15,146
10 years?

539
00:32:16,850 --> 00:32:17,822
And you even have to study abroad?

540
00:32:19,697 --> 00:32:21,693
I would not be able to see you for a long time.

541
00:32:24,983 --> 00:32:29,040
But first, I have to get into the Marine Science Programme at Kasetsart University.

542
00:32:29,616 --> 00:32:32,906
